MozRepl: differentiating among creation, host and work context.

- creation context is the toplevel where the repl is created;

- host context is where 'repl' (or whatever its name) is looked up;
  initially this is the same of the creation context; if user enters
  another toplevel, though, we clone the repl there to ensure it is
  still available;

- work context is where code is evaluated;

- when repl is renamed, change is made to the creation context and
  current host context.

